  <section id="intro">
    <title id="intro_title">Introduction</title>

    <para>
     The purpose of this document is to describe how to enable @gold_edition@.
    </para>
   </section>
   <section>
	   <title>@gold_edition@</title>
	   <para>		   
		<emphasis>@gold_edition@</emphasis> is a comprehensive platform designed to deliver solutions for workforce mobility, BYOD initiatives, desktop virtual projects and more. It comprises advanced features such as an SSL Gateway and two factor authentication support for enhanced security and integration to Microsoft SharePoint and Alfresco. It delivers seamless applications and desktop sessions from Windows and Linux servers to native Windows and Linux clients, HTML5 enabled browsers and mobile devices. A fully featured administrator web console provides for configuration of server settings, user management, application publishing and server monitoring along with server load balancing for optimum performance and scalability.		
			<!--
			TBD This file needs to be re-written to take into account the new language being used for PE. 
			-->
			<para>
				The <emphasis>@gold_edition@</emphasis> allows the users to enable @gold_edition@ features such as SmartCard support 
				and enables users to connect using a <emphasis>@gold_edition@</emphasis> client. 
				Ulteo provides the following <emphasis>@gold_edition@</emphasis> clients:
				<itemizedlist>
				<listitem>
				<para><ulink url="NativeClient.html">Native Client for Windows and Linux</ulink></para>
				</listitem>
				 <listitem>
				 <para>iOS Client</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
				 <para>Android Client</para>
				</listitem>
				</itemizedlist>
				The OVD Gateway is also available as part of the <emphasis>@gold_edition@</emphasis>. For more information on the Gateway, please refer to the documentation on the 
				<ulink url="Installation_Gateway_Precise.html">OVD Gateway</ulink>				 
				
				
			</para>		 
	   </para>
   </section>
    <section id="community">
    <title id="intro_community">Installation</title>     		 		     
        <note>
			<para>The Premium module is available on all the supported distributions.</para>			
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem>Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6</listitem>
				<listitem>SUSE Linux Enterprise Server 11.SP1</listitem>
				<listitem>Ubuntu Lucid</listitem>				
				<listitem>Ubuntu Precise</listitem>	
				<listitem>Debian Squeeze</listitem>
				<listitem>Debian Wheezy</listitem>				
				<listitem>OpenSUSE 11.3</listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
        </note>  
         <section>			
			<title>Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6</title>
			 <itemizedlist>
		<listitem> 			
			<para>Edit the file <emphasis>/etc/yum.repos.d/ovd.premium.repo</emphasis> with:</para>        
          <screen>
<![CDATA[[ovd-@VERSIONNOTILD@]
name=Ulteo OVD @VERSION@
baseurl=@BASE_URI_GOLD@/rhel/@distrib_version_r@/
enabled=1
gpgcheck=1
gpgkey=@BASE_URI@/rhel/@distrib_version_r@/keyring]]>
          </screen>
          </listitem>
          <listitem>
           <para>			  
          You have to install the Premium module <emphasis>ulteo-ovd-session-manager-premium</emphasis>:
        </para>
        <screen>
<![CDATA[
# yum install ulteo-ovd-session-manager-premium]]>
        </screen>        
        </listitem>
         </itemizedlist>
        </section>
         <section>			
			<title>SUSE Linux Enterprise Server 11.SP1</title>
			 <itemizedlist>
		<listitem> 			
			<para>Add the Premium repository: </para>        
          <screen>
<![CDATA[# zypper ar @BASE_URI_GOLD@/@distrib_name_sl@/@distrib_version_sl@ ovd
# zypper refresh]]>
          </screen>
          </listitem>
          <listitem>
           <para>			  
          You have to install the Premium module <emphasis>ulteo-ovd-session-manager-premium</emphasis>:
        </para>
        <screen>
<![CDATA[
# zypper install ulteo-ovd-session-manager-premium]]>
        </screen>        
        </listitem>
         </itemizedlist>
        </section>      
        <section>			
			<title>Ubuntu Lucid</title>
			 <itemizedlist>
		<listitem>
          <xi:include href="&base;" xpointer="repository_online_step1_para" />
          <screen>
<![CDATA[deb @BASE_URI@/@distrib_name_l@ @distrib_version_l@ main
deb @BASE_URI_GOLD@/@distrib_name_l@ @distrib_version_l@ main]]>
          </screen>
          </listitem>
          <listitem>
           <para>			  
          You have to install the Premium module <emphasis>ulteo-ovd-session-manager-premium</emphasis>:
        </para>
        <screen>
<![CDATA[# apt-get update
# apt-get install ulteo-ovd-session-manager-premium]]>
        </screen>
        </listitem>
         </itemizedlist>
        </section>
